{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3401389,"name":"Chris Yahnker","username":"cyahnker","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/c5a1d2/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-06-23T20:32:07.686Z","cooked":"

Hi everyone,

Team 691 here. This was our first year using swerve, and we ran the Rev MAXSwerve modules (3in MAXSwerve Module - REV Robotics). We had good overall performance, especially after switching to aluminum wheels.

For next season, we’re interested in upgrading our drivetrain’s performance. Our drive team is specifically eyeing the Kraken motors.

Has anyone successfully swapped out the motors on the Rev modules for Krakens? If so, what was the level of difficulty, especially for a team like ours that mostly builds parts by hand with limited CNC machining?

We’re also considering buying a new swerve kit altogether, like the WCP Swerve X (Swerve X – WestCoast Products). It seems like a solid option, but we’d love to hear thoughts on whether modifying our existing Rev modules is worth pursuing.

Since we’re planning to buy new kits anyway (last year’s got pretty worn out), we’re open to sticking with what we know and modifying, or trying something completely different. Any advice or experiences you can share would be greatly appreciated!

Thanks!
